article.headline: Hampton 87, MD Eastern Shore 75
article.story: PRINCESS ANNE, Md. (AP) -- Bruce Brown led four Hampton players in double figures with 18 points and 13 rebounds as Maryland-Eastern Shore fell 87-75 Saturday. Jeff Granger had 17 points on 6-of-10 shooting and 5-of-6 three-point shooting for Hampton (9-9,7-3 Mid-Eastern Atlantic Conference). Jaz Cowan also had 17 points and Rashad West added 12 points for the Pirates. Antonio McMillion had 21 points on 10-of-13 shooting for the Hawks (5-15, 2-8) and Troy Jackson added another 16 points. Jesse Brooks shot 5-of-11 to finish with 14 points. Ed Tyson also had 14 points. The Pirates led 38-31 at halftime after shooting 55 percent compared to the Hawks shooting 37 percent from the floor.
